properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 11 at 3:56AM CST until January 11 at 6:00PM CST by NWS Des Moines IA
properties.description:
...More Snow Southeast Today...

.Only patchy light snow or flurries linger over southeast Iowa
early this morning, but more snow is expected there later today.
Several more inches are possible with hazardous travel continuing.

* WHAT...Snow. Additional snow accumulations of one to two inches.
Little if any additional freezing rain.

* WHERE....Portions of central and southeast Iowa.

* WHEN...Until 6 PM CST this evening, with peak snowfall from
midday through late afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Expect hazardous travel with roads remaining
partially to completely snow covered and low visibilities during
periods of heavier snow.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.
